Ask HN: What is the point of smartphone wireless chargers?
text:
I get that manufacturers are happy to sell more crap, and consumers are happy to buy new shiny crap. And wireless chargers are more expensive than wires, so that's an incentive for the manufacturer.

But technically, is it really worth making wireless chargers? It seems to me that they are strictly more complex, require more material, charge slower and are less energy efficient. Moreover, they still require a wire: instead of plugging it into the phone, you align its magnetic end to the magnet on the phone.

So is there an actual technical argument in favour of wireless chargers? Like is it that hard to make a waterproof usb socket that it justifies wasting material and energy with a radically different approach?

title: Ask HN: Training LLM Tutorial
text:
I’m looking for any tutorials on how to train a LLM model like LLaMa or similar for educational reasons? I imagine something like giving it a bunch of books to be able to generate similar content.

I’m ok with buying some GPU instances for a short period of time if that’s required. Any step by step tutorials are much appreciated !

Ask HN: Is Gmail/Google Workspace getting slower?
text:
I am getting the impression that gmail is not as snappy as it used to be. Like it takes longer to open the page, to search for emails, and to open an email draft. I will not have time to migrate to another email platform anytime soon, but I am thinking about it. For the time being, I wonder if it could be something else. Maybe I have too many old emails? It's ~7,000 at the moment, that should not be too much. Or maybe it's my connection. Or maybe I have just been reading too many negative things about google, and I start imagining things?

edit: Just checked, and it takes 12 seconds to launch it.
